Huh?

35
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:52,590
What's that about?

36
00:02:53,700 --> 00:02:55,830
Wow.

37
00:03:01,030 --> 00:03:04,940
My bride looks so beautiful today.

38
00:03:08,530 --> 00:03:10,120
W-What did you say?

39
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:12,570
The wedding is happening right now?

40
00:03:12,570 --> 00:03:15,410
Hey, hey. No. It can't.

41
00:03:15,410 --> 00:03:17,540
No, Soo Jin!

42
00:03:17,540 --> 00:03:19,630
Hey! Hey, Soo Jin!

43
00:03:19,630 --> 00:03:23,270
Soo Jin, you can't marry him!

44
00:03:23,270 --> 00:03:25,760
No, you can't...

45
00:03:25,760 --> 00:03:29,140
No! This marriage is invalid.

46
00:03:29,140 --> 00:03:32,210
This marriage is invalid!

47
00:03:32,210 --> 00:03:34,600
You scared me.

48
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:36,890
Hey, be quiet.

49
00:03:41,090 --> 00:03:43,060
Hey, Seok Tae.

50
00:03:43,060 --> 00:03:45,080
What year is this?

51
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:49,030
Hey, I've known you all my life but I'm still having a hard time getting used to you.

52
00:03:49,030 --> 00:03:51,260
What do you mean what year is this?! It's 2014.

53
00:03:51,260 --> 00:03:53,930
20..14?!

54
00:03:54,870 --> 00:03:57,700
2014...

55
00:03:57,700 --> 00:04:02,320
If this is 2014, then it hasn't been long since I got discharged from the military.

56
00:04:04,470 --> 00:04:07,770
Then why did I see Soo Jin's wedding all of a sudden?

57
00:04:08,430 --> 00:04:12,490
So, does this mean that Soo Jin's wedding is still going on in the present?

58
00:04:13,570 --> 00:04:16,340
Man, this is driving me crazy.

59
00:04:16,340 --> 00:04:18,890
Hey, Seok Tae.

60
00:04:18,890 --> 00:04:20,320
What's Soo Jin up to these days?

61
00:04:20,320 --> 00:04:23,640
What do you mean what is she doing? She's working as an assistant at that photography studio.

62
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:28,410
Oh yeah, that's right.

63
00:04:29,060 --> 00:04:31,120
Hey...

64
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:33,430
What are you doing there anyway?

65
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:39,070
By the way, what are you going to get for Jin Sook's birthday?

66
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:40,810
Jin Sook?

67
00:04:40,810 --> 00:04:43,280
Jin Sook...

68
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:48,050
 Why are you taking my sincere feelings as a joke? 

69
00:04:48,050 --> 00:04:53,090
 I'm being serious when I say that I like you. I've liked you ever since high school. 

70
00:04:54,630 --> 00:04:57,300
There's no way you forgot about Jin Sook's birthday today, right?

71
00:04:57,300 --> 00:04:58,990
Jin Sook, please don't.

72
00:04:58,990 --> 00:05:01,460
What are you talking about? You're being like this because you don't have money again, huh?

73
00:05:01,460 --> 00:05:04,530
A future civil servant who doesn't have any money. Jin Sook will understand that.

74
00:05:04,530 --> 00:05:07,730
Your thought is what will count and that's plenty enough.

75
00:05:07,730 --> 00:05:12,300
I have to somehow turn Jin Sook's feeling around no matter what.

76
00:05:12,300 --> 00:05:14,840
That's what I have to do.

77
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:18,360
Seriously, how am I suppose to face Jin Sook like this?

78
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:21,420
   

79
00:05:21,420 --> 00:05:24,970
   

80
00:05:40,550 --> 00:05:42,750
So hot!

81
00:05:58,510 --> 00:06:00,870
It's done.

82
00:06:15,230 --> 00:06:18,100
Three years ago?

83
00:06:18,100 --> 00:06:20,100
Why of all times does it have to be now?

84
00:06:20,100 --> 00:06:23,510
It would've been nice if you just sent me back to high school while you're at it.

85
00:06:23,510 --> 00:06:27,960
Then I could've come up with something to do about this.

86
00:06:31,710 --> 00:06:35,370
What am I supposed to do and where am I supposed to start?

87
00:06:38,760 --> 00:06:42,850
Hey, be careful with your steps. Careful now.

88
00:06:42,850 --> 00:06:44,260
What's this fuss about?

89
00:06:44,260 --> 00:06:46,640
Stop!

90
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:48,410
Ta-da!

91
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:52,440
Happy birthday, Sook.

92
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:57,730
Hey. When did you prepare all this?

93
00:06:57,730 --> 00:07:01,120
Gosh, girl. Don't you have a photo shoot to go to today? You're not going to be late?

94
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:04,610
Look, my friend comes first before my work, okay?

95
00:07:04,610 --> 00:07:08,770
Have I ever skipped making your birthday meal? Have a seat there.

96
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:16,470
I made all your favorite dishes including buIgogi ( marinated beef )  and  japchae ( glass noodles ).

97
00:07:17,300 --> 00:07:21,710
Kang Soo Jin, thank you so much.

98
00:07:21,710 --> 00:07:25,820
My grandma always worried for me. She was afraid that I'd be celebrating my birthday all alone.

99
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:30,010
Please tell your grandma not to worry.

100
00:07:30,010 --> 00:07:33,320
I will take care of your birthday meals for the rest of my life.

101
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:36,330
Let's cancel the "rest of my life" part.

102
00:07:36,330 --> 00:07:40,010
I'm sure when I get a boyfriend, he'll do all this for me too.

103
00:07:40,010 --> 00:07:42,460
Oh, is that right?

104
00:07:42,460 --> 00:07:47,010
Then you should say that after you get yourself a boyfriend.

105
00:07:47,010 --> 00:07:50,940
What's with that reaction, you old lady?

106
00:07:50,940 --> 00:07:56,140
It would be so awesome if the heavens gave me a boyfriend as a birthday present.

107
00:07:56,140 --> 00:08:01,370
You shouldn't look up to the sky for a boyfriend but you should look more closely around you instead.

108
00:08:01,370 --> 00:08:06,100
I wonder if there is a nice guy out there for you?

109
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:12,070
Hey, eat first!

110
00:08:12,070 --> 00:08:15,460
I will sing you the birthday son—

111
00:08:15,460 --> 00:08:17,500
Thanks for the food.

112
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:20,470
Why is it that I never get to sing the birthday song each year?

113
00:08:20,470 --> 00:08:22,830
Hey, Kang Soo Jin.

114
00:08:22,830 --> 00:08:25,080
This is so delicious.

115
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:27,930
You should be a chef instead of a photographer.

116
00:08:27,930 --> 00:08:29,530
Does it taste okay?

117
00:08:29,530 --> 00:08:34,770
Alright, I'm going recruit  you to work for me at my shop. Let's write up a contract.

118
00:08:34,770 --> 00:08:37,160
Stop it! You always talk about the same thing everyday.

119
00:08:37,160 --> 00:08:39,220
Why not?! 
     

120
00:08:39,220 --> 00:08:42,210
Oh, why not? It's so good though. Why, why, why?

121
00:08:42,210 --> 00:08:45,530
I told you, I'm okay!

122
00:08:45,530 --> 00:08:49,200
- Even though I made it, I have to say it does taste good.
- You're so shameless.

123
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:51,700
It tastes so great, so great!

124
00:08:52,940 --> 00:08:55,260
How should I solve the misunderstanding with Soo Jin?

125
00:08:55,260 --> 00:08:58,610
And how should I change Jin Sook's feelings?

126
00:09:04,450 --> 00:09:06,890
   

127
00:09:06,890 --> 00:09:09,640
What should I do about this?

128
00:09:09,640 --> 00:09:13,080
Should I just go over to Jin Sook and ask for it?

129
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:16,570
No, I shouldn't. Jin Sook might try to confess to me again.

130
00:09:16,570 --> 00:09:18,700
What would I do then?

131
00:09:23,870 --> 00:09:28,000
Oh, that's right. It's the past right now, huh?

132
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:32,580
Then the fact that Jin Sook took the letters could be reset.

133
00:09:33,660 --> 00:09:35,170
Yeah, okay.

134
00:09:35,170 --> 00:09:37,330
Pil!

135
00:09:37,330 --> 00:09:39,170
Hello.

136
00:09:39,170 --> 00:09:41,980
I haven't seen you in a while.

137
00:09:41,980 --> 00:09:44,910
I guess it's because you've been studying, right?

138
00:09:44,910 --> 00:09:47,430
Yes, it's time for me to grow up now.

139
00:09:47,430 --> 00:09:52,460
That's a good idea. They say that when a person matures, they die—

140
00:09:52,460 --> 00:09:55,300
Oh my, what am I talking about?

141
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:58,930
But why are you so awkward with Soo Jin?

142
00:09:58,930 --> 00:10:02,390
- I thought that maybe you two had a fight. 
 - Pardon?

143
00:10:02,390 --> 00:10:07,430
Ever since you came back from the military, Soo Jin's face would freeze up whenever anyone talked about you.

144
00:10:07,430 --> 00:10:09,810
And I could sense that she hates you—

145
00:10:09,810 --> 00:10:12,370
Oh my. What am I saying?

146
00:10:12,370 --> 00:10:16,530
Anyway, be good friends with my Soo Jin. Come over sometime too.

147
00:10:16,530 --> 00:10:18,950
I'll get going.

148
00:10:23,090 --> 00:10:26,340
So Soo Jin is mad at me.

149
00:10:26,340 --> 00:10:30,110
It must be because she didn't receive my reply letters.

150
00:10:30,110 --> 00:10:34,000
First, let's find the letters. There's no other answer but that.

151
00:10:36,690 --> 00:10:40,440
I'm going to take the picture!

152
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:44,020
Groom, bride, you don't look affectionate! These pictures will exist forever!

153
00:10:44,020 --> 00:10:47,700
Here, I'm taking the picture! Get ready!

154
00:10:49,740 --> 00:10:54,010
That's not it. Wedding pictures should show tenderness.

155
00:10:54,010 --> 00:10:56,590
Put your hand on your bride's waist.

156
00:10:56,590 --> 00:11:00,020
- Sunbae!
- Oh, you're here?

157
00:11:00,020 --> 00:11:02,920
Sit down.

158
00:11:05,680 --> 00:11:10,160
I am the happiest person in the world!

159
00:11:11,760 --> 00:11:14,230
Here! Next is kiss time!

160
00:11:14,230 --> 00:11:16,250
Kiss or a peck?

161
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:18,870
A little more.

162
00:11:18,870 --> 00:11:22,310
One, two!

163
00:11:22,310 --> 00:11:24,220
Three! Oh my!

164
00:11:25,250 --> 00:11:26,430
Hello.

165
00:11:26,430 --> 00:11:30,200
Oh, hello. Wait a moment.

166
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:33,590
Groom and bride, let's take a break before we continue. Drink some water.

167
00:11:33,590 --> 00:11:35,310
Thank you!

168
00:11:35,310 --> 00:11:38,300
You are different than usual when you're working.

169
00:11:38,300 --> 00:11:40,270
It's cool.

170
00:11:42,770 --> 00:11:46,120
- I guess you're not working at the pharmacy today.
- Ah—

171
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:50,430
It's Jae Hyeon's off day today, so I asked him to come along.

172
00:11:50,430 --> 00:11:52,670
I did so he can have some fresh air.

173
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:54,500
Did I disturb you?

174
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:56,460
No, none of the sort.

175
00:11:56,460 --> 00:11:58,270
Should we all have a meal together?

176
00:11:58,270 --> 00:11:59,960
That sounds good.

177
00:12:01,110 --> 00:12:05,410
I forgot I had an appointment for lunch.

178
00:12:05,410 --> 00:12:07,680
Pardon?

179
00:12:07,680 --> 00:12:10,010
This became complicated.

180
00:12:10,010 --> 00:12:13,330
Jae Hyeon, it looks like you can eat lunch with Soo Jin.

181
00:12:13,330 --> 00:12:15,720
- Jae Hyeon, I'll request this of you! 
 - Okay.

182
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:18,520
CEO! C-CEO!

183
00:12:21,540 --> 00:12:24,990
W-Why is the CEO like that? R-Really...

184
00:12:24,990 --> 00:12:28,300
Since it turned out this way, let's eat lunch together.

185
00:12:28,300 --> 00:12:31,080
I brought sandwiches.

186
00:12:32,040 --> 00:12:34,090
The two of us?

187
00:12:36,470 --> 00:12:38,110
Just the two of us...

188
00:12:45,270 --> 00:12:47,520
What should I do?

189
00:13:22,050 --> 00:13:26,070
What the heck? Why isn't it here?

190
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:29,840
I hid it here.

191
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:41,820
Ah, that's right. This is the past.

192
00:13:51,510 --> 00:13:55,570
 Trash like you cannot enter. 

193
00:13:58,310 --> 00:14:00,580
Hold on.

194
00:14:03,220 --> 00:14:05,700
That's right.

195
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:21,710
Jin Sook, I'm sorry. I didn't want to go to this extent, but

196
00:14:21,710 --> 00:14:23,900
I can't help it.

197
00:14:23,900 --> 00:14:27,760
I'll try to be mindful of your privacy.

198
00:14:27,760 --> 00:14:31,700
I'll just look for the letters. Just the letters.

199
00:14:32,890 --> 00:14:35,350
It was here somewhere.

200
00:14:51,910 --> 00:14:56,680
Jin Sook, why do you like someone like me?

201
00:15:03,170 --> 00:15:06,050
- Be calm.
- Hey!

202
00:15:09,660 --> 00:15:11,360
What are you doing here?

203
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:13,120
Oh.

204
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:17,730
I thought it was your birthday so I came to make you seaweed soup (tradition on birthdays).

205
00:15:17,730 --> 00:15:19,970
Without the seaweed?

206
00:15:20,760 --> 00:15:22,830
Oh, you're right.

207
00:15:22,830 --> 00:15:25,070
I must've left the seaweed at home.

208
00:15:25,070 --> 00:15:27,980
I'll bring the seaweed.

209
00:15:27,980 --> 00:15:31,170
Hey. Be honest.

210
00:15:31,170 --> 00:15:33,720
Did you come to my house...

211
00:15:34,190 --> 00:15:36,630
You came to steal my secret fund, right?

212
00:15:36,630 --> 00:15:39,970
Hey! Let's not do that, between friends.

213
00:15:39,970 --> 00:15:42,640
Hey, what are you talking about?

214
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:45,100
I came to make you seaweed soup.

215
00:15:45,100 --> 00:15:46,690
Really?

216
00:15:46,690 --> 00:15:48,330
I don't think so. Let me look.

217
00:15:48,330 --> 00:15:53,470
- I said I didn't!
- Look, here! Right here!

218
00:16:10,100 --> 00:16:13,240
Hey. I told you I really didn't.

219
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:18,150
Anyway, I'm going to go get the seaweed. I'll see you later.

220
